<div id="review_3521705707" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3521705707" />
    <a title="Nahla" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44565830-nahla"><img alt="Nahla" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610494991p2/44565830.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3521705707?book_show_action=true">Aug 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nahla" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nahla" href="/user/show/44565830-nahla">Nahla</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/700479.The_Story_of_Layla_and_Majnun">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3521705707" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17756228471606955615">3,5 <br/>The beauty in the verse is incomparable to anything I’ve read before. I am rather sad that I couldn’t read the Persian version for it is I’m sure exquisite. The story of Layla and Majnun is presented as a Romeo and Juliet of Middle East but I think It should be the other way around. The novel is rather short as it is the translation of five poems by Nizami. <br/>More than the prose, I adored the environment and metaphors for literally everything.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

