        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3771136330" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6044752129911231026">Love is a delicate, complicated subject across cultures. But whenever one talks about the depth of love, the intensity of passion, two names almost immediately come to mind- Layla and Majnun. <br/>Two in flesh but one in spirit. Such is the story of Layla Majnun written by the famous Persian poet Nizami Ganjavi.<br/> It is the true story of a young man by the name Qays who belonged to the Umayyad era during the 7th century in northern Arabian Peninsula. Like every tragic love story, this story too is lade</span>
  <span id="freeText6044752129911231026" style="display:none">Love is a delicate, complicated subject across cultures. But whenever one talks about the depth of love, the intensity of passion, two names almost immediately come to mind- Layla and Majnun. <br />Two in flesh but one in spirit. Such is the story of Layla Majnun written by the famous Persian poet Nizami Ganjavi.<br /> It is the true story of a young man by the name Qays who belonged to the Umayyad era during the 7th century in northern Arabian Peninsula. Like every tragic love story, this story too is laden with passion and grief over separation. <br />Layla, belonging to a wealthy tribe by fate falls in love with Qays, a poet, who too loves her dearly. However their union is not accepted by her parents who marry her off to a wealthy man.<br /> Forbiddance to meet each other anymore takes a toll on both the lovers. While Qays transforms into Majnun, literally to be driven mad in love, leaving the comfort of his home, wandering from place to place, reciting poems for his lover. Layla also became devastated, denying her husband any marital pleasures and staying loyal to her lover till the end of her life. <br />While the lovers neither marry nor consummate their love, they still remain devoted and faithful to each other. Their eyes might not have the chance to talk to each other but their hearts are always in sync. <br />The lovers are finally united when Majnun breathes his last near the grave of Layla. And beside him, on the rock, were inscribed the last three of his verses, dedicated to his love Layla.<br /> It is the most beautiful tale of true, invincible, unyielding, passionate love.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/67397.Layla_and_Majnun" title="Layla and Majnun by Nizami Ganjavi" rel="nofollow noopener">Layla and Majnun</a><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/91847.Nizami_Ganjavi" title="Nizami Ganjavi" rel="nofollow noopener">Nizami Ganjavi</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="6044752129911231026" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


