        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3425377388" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4339081061793234879">The talent of both Nizami and Colin Turner is undoubtable throughout, with the affinity for language clearly masterful even down to the nuanced conveyance of every didactic aphorism filled with sage wisdom about different facets of mortality employed by Nizami throughout. However ,despite understanding the profound premise and enjoying the elegant packaging - I found this tale of star-crossed lovers more frustrating than even Romeo and Juliet due to the extent of hyperbole.<br/><br/><br/>Despite his all-encomp</span>
  <span id="freeText4339081061793234879" style="display:none">The talent of both Nizami and Colin Turner is undoubtable throughout, with the affinity for language clearly masterful even down to the nuanced conveyance of every didactic aphorism filled with sage wisdom about different facets of mortality employed by Nizami throughout. However ,despite understanding the profound premise and enjoying the elegant packaging - I found this tale of star-crossed lovers more frustrating than even Romeo and Juliet due to the extent of hyperbole.<br /><br /><br />Despite his all-encompassing obsession with her, Layla appears somewhat of a flat character (particularly with the androcentric narrative, she is barely elaborated upon enough besides her unparalleled beauty) to be worthy of such a lengthy and traumatic journey on her behalf. <br />​<br /><br />At about midway (as a pragmatist) his senseless reluctance to seek out even personal comfort was extremely frustrating to read despite acknowledging the tragedy it appears largely self-inflicted, exacerbated by hysteria and self-indulgence. Instead, despite her diminished narratorial voice, Layla provides the most realistic tale with her less ostentatious grief and gestures of love. <br /><br />If you want to see more on this review or others check out my book blog: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://getthelowdown.wixsite.com/mysite">getthelowdown.wixsite.com/mysite</a> </span>
  <a data-text-id="4339081061793234879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


