<span id="freeTextContainer16367921920028049010">The most beautiful tale of true, invinvible, unyielding, passionate love.<br/>A true literature masterpiece.<br/>Although I&apos;m well aware that probably a lot of Nizami Ganjavi&apos;s genius was lost in translation, as is often the case with literature (especially poems), I was absolutely stunned by the piece. <br/>Any review, all attempts to describe such a work, naturally seem bleak and out of place.<br/>I only wish that more poeple knew of this amazing work, this story should be known all over the world, for it definit</span>
  <span id="freeText16367921920028049010" style="display:none">The most beautiful tale of true, invinvible, unyielding, passionate love.<br />A true literature masterpiece.<br />Although I'm well aware that probably a lot of Nizami Ganjavi's genius was lost in translation, as is often the case with literature (especially poems), I was absolutely stunned by the piece. <br />Any review, all attempts to describe such a work, naturally seem bleak and out of place.<br />I only wish that more poeple knew of this amazing work, this story should be known all over the world, for it definitely deserves the fame no less than any classic love stories like those of Shakespeare's "Romeo and Juliette" for instance. <br />~~~"Nizami's strain is sung:<br />The Persian poet's pearls are strong;<br />then fill again the goblet high!<br />Thou wouldst not ask the reveller why!<br />Fill to the love that changes never!<br />Fill to the love that lives for ever!"~~~</span>
